# PlantUML Diagrams

Use PlantUML for all architecture and flow diagrams. Embed the source directly in each markdown file. Do not use separate `.puml` files.

## Markdown convention

The image tag appears first (visible). The PlantUML source is hidden in a `<details>` block. The `@startuml` line includes the output path: `@startuml diagrams/name`. PlantUML writes to `diagrams/name.png` in the same directory as the markdown file.

```markdown
![Diagram Title](diagrams/name.png)

<details>
<summary>PlantUML source</summary>

```
@startuml diagrams/name
...diagram content...
@enduml
```

</details>
```

Use plain fenced code blocks (not `plantuml` language tag). PlantUML finds `@startuml`/`@enduml` by text scan.

## Do NOT use HTML comments or hidden divs for PlantUML source

The `-->` arrow in PlantUML breaks HTML comment parsing (`<!-- -->`). Use `<details>` blocks instead — they safely contain any PlantUML syntax.

## Regenerating images

Run `./script/render-diagrams` to regenerate all diagrams, or `./script/render-diagrams docs/path/to/file.md` for a single file. The script installs `plantuml` via apt if not already present. Commit the generated PNGs so GitHub renders them.

## C4 diagrams

PlantUML's stdlib includes C4 macros. Use:

- `!include <C4/C4_Context>` for context diagrams
- `!include <C4/C4_Container>` for container diagrams
- `!include <C4/C4_Component>` for component diagrams

Example:

```
@startuml diagrams/system-context
!include <C4/C4_Context>

Person(user, "Insurance Manager", "Manages family claims")
System(coordinate, "Coordinate PWA", "Local-first web app")
System_Ext(insurer, "Insurer Portals", "Sun Life, Manulife, etc.")

Rel(user, coordinate, "Uses")
Rel(user, insurer, "Submits claims")
@enduml
```
